  <main>
    <% var videoName ="";
    var videoUrl ="";
    if(todayVideo == null) {
      videoName = "Not uploaded Yet";
  }
  else{
    videoName = todayVideo.videoName;
    videoUrl = todayVideo.videoUrl;
  }
  %>
    <section class="daily-motivation">
      <div class="daily-motivation-container">
        <div class="daily-motivation-content">
          <h1>Daily Motivational <br> Video</h1>
          <p><%= videoName.replace('.mp4',"") %></p>
          <a target="_blank" href="<%= videoUrl%>"><button>Play Now</button></a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="all-videos">

      <div class="all-videos-card-container">
        <div class="all-videos-card-content" id="cardContent">
          <% for(let i = 0; i < videos.length; i++) { %>
            <div class="cardd">
              <a target="_blank" href="<%= videos[i].videoUrl  %>">
                <div class="card-bg" style="background-color: <%= colors[i] %>;">
                    <% 
                        let date = new Date(videos[i].videoName.replace('.mp4',""));
                        let formattedDate = date.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { day: 'numeric', month: 'long', year: 'numeric' });
                    %>
                    <h1> <%= formattedDate %> </h1>
                </div>
              </a>
            </div>
        <% } %>
        </div>
        <div class="btn-container">
          <div class="scrollLeftBtn" id="scrollLeftBtn">
            <img src="images/left-arrow.png" alt="">

          </div>
          <div class="scrollRightBtn" id="scrollRightBtn">
            <img src="images/right-arrow.png" alt="">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <script>
      document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
        const cardContainer = document.getElementById('cardContent');
        const scrollLeftBtn = document.getElementById('scrollLeftBtn');
        const scrollRightBtn = document.getElementById('scrollRightBtn');

        scrollLeftBtn.addEventListener('click', function () {
          const scrollAmount = -300;
          smoothScroll(cardContainer, scrollAmount);
        });

        scrollRightBtn.addEventListener('click', function () {
          const scrollAmount = 300;
          smoothScroll(cardContainer, scrollAmount);
        });

        function smoothScroll(element, scrollAmount) {
          const startPosition = element.scrollLeft;
          const targetScroll = startPosition + scrollAmount;
          const distance = Math.abs(scrollAmount);
          const duration = 300;
          const direction = scrollAmount > 0 ? 1 : -1;
          let startTime;

          function scroll(timestamp) {
            startTime = startTime || timestamp;
            const elapsed = timestamp - startTime;
            const progress = Math.min(elapsed / duration, 1);

            element.scrollLeft = startPosition + direction * progress * distance;

            if (progress < 1) {
              window.requestAnimationFrame(scroll);
            }
          }

          window.requestAnimationFrame(scroll);
        }
      });

    </script>


    <section class="mudras">
      <div class="mudras-container">
        <div class="mudras-content">
          <h1>Mudras</h1>
          <div class="mudras-card-content">
            <div class="mudra-card" id="mudra-card-1" onclick="openDialog(1,1)">
              <div class="img-container">
                <img src="images/akash-mudra.png" alt="">
              </div>
              <h3>Akash Mudra</h3>
              <p>Akash Mudra also known as the "Space Mudra" or "Aakash Mudra," is a hand gesture or mudra used in yoga
                and
                meditation practices.</p>

            </div>
            <div class="dialog" id="dialog-1">
              <div class="dialog-content">
                <span class="close" id="close-1" onclick="closeDialog(1)">&times;</span>
                <h1>Akash Mudra</h1>
                <p>Akash Mudra
                  also known as the "Space Mudra" or "Aakash Mudra," is a hand gesture or mudra used in yoga and
                  meditation practices. It is believed to help balance the element of space (akash) within the body and
                  promote a sense of calmness, openness, and expansiveness.
                </p>
                <h4>To perform Akash Mudra:</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>Start by sitting in a comfortable meditation posture, such as cross-legged on the floor or in a
                    chair with your spine straight.</li>
                  <li>Relax your hands on your knees or thighs.</li>
                  <li>Bring your arms in front of your chest, keeping your elbows bent and close to your body.</li>
                  <li>Join the tips of your middle finger and thumb, creating a circle or ring shape. The other fingers
                    should be extended and pointing upward.</li>
                  <li>Keep your wrists relaxed and your hands comfortably resting in front of your chest.</li>
                  <li>Take slow, deep breaths and allow yourself to feel a sense of spaciousness and openness.
                  </li>
                  <li>Hold the mudra for several minutes or as long as feels comfortable and beneficial.</li>
                </ul>
                <h4>Benefits : </h4>
                <p>Expands consciousness, improves intuition, enhances mental clarity.</p>
                <h4>Release:</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>Gently separate your middle finger and thumb, releasing the circle or ring shape created by
                    joining their tips.</li>
                  <li>Allow your fingers to naturally unfold and extend.</li>
                  <li>Relax your hands on your knees or thighs.</li>
                  <li>letting them rest in a comfortable position.</li>
                  <li>Take a moment to observe any sensations or shifts in your energy after releasing the mudra.</li>
                  <li>If you wish, you can take a few deep breaths or continue with your meditation or yoga practice.
                  </li>
                </ul>
                <h4>Duration : </h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>Practice for 10-15 minutes daily.</li>
                  <li>You can extend it to 40-45 minutes Daily.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>

          

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

